# vibe-glm-ocr.env.tmpl — rendered to /opt/vibe/env/vibe-glm-ocr.env
# by lib/enable-app.sh. No DATABASE_URL, no REDIS_URL — this app uses
# neither. The upstream image is llama.cpp's llama-server serving the
# GLM-OCR F16 GGUF model; it reads only the OCR_* vars below.

# --- Optional tuning knobs (override via 'sudo nano /opt/vibe/env/vibe-glm-ocr.env') ---
#
# OCR_THREADS — `llama-server --threads`. Default 4. llama.cpp's CPU
# inference is memory-bandwidth-bound, not CPU-bound, past ~physical-core
# count; over-threading typically hurts latency rather than helping it.
# Match this to physical cores (not threads — hyperthreaded logical
# cores share bandwidth). On a 1-vCPU droplet leave at 4 default or
# lower to 2; on a 4-physical-core host try 4 first, increase only with
# measurement. `nproc` on the host overcounts on hyperthreaded CPUs.
# OCR_THREADS=4
#
# OCR_PARALLEL — `llama-server --parallel`. Default 2 concurrent slots.
# Each slot doubles working-set memory (additional KV cache per slot)
# and divides CPU among in-flight requests. Lower to 1 on memory-tight
# hosts to halve peak RAM; raise on 8 GB+ hosts to absorb burst load
# without queueing. Throughput vs. latency tradeoff is genuine — single
# requests are slowest at parallel=8.
# OCR_PARALLEL=2
#
# OCR_CTX_SIZE — `llama-server --ctx-size`. Default 32768 tokens. OCR
# pipelines rarely need long context (you're processing image patches,
# not transcripts). Reducing to 8192 cuts KV-cache memory ~4x with no
# quality impact for typical receipt / invoice / W-2 pages. Increase
# only if you're processing multi-page documents in a single request.
# OCR_CTX_SIZE=32768
#
# OCR_TEMPERATURE — `llama-server --temp`. Default 0.02 (near-greedy).
# Tuned upstream for OCR determinism. Do not raise unless you're
# specifically testing output variation.
# OCR_TEMPERATURE=0.02
#
# OCR_API_KEY — `llama-server --api-key`. Default unset. Set to require
# clients to send `Authorization: Bearer <key>` on every request. Most
# appliances don't need this because vibe-glm-ocr is only reachable on
# vibe_net (internal docker network); set it if you're exposing the
# port externally for some reason.
# OCR_API_KEY=
